Django Website update history
===========================================================================================================
Update 5/10/2017: -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Added database Fields
- Now working with MySQL
- Added Index Page/Home Page
- Added Admin edit Page (django edit)
- Working Index Page
- Added Navigation Bar
- Navigation bar is scalable (usable when window size is reduced)
- Added Details Page
Update 14/10/2017: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Fixed Details Page not showing Data
- Error handling: 404 Page not found e.g. when typing a non-exsistant ID in URL
- Added Login Template
Update 16/10/2017: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Added Registration form: type in ".../register" at the end of the URL
- Added feature to upload images rather than typing url
- developer mode: saves all images to a folder when in development
- Database edited to avoid repetition ("location_detail" table)
Update 25/10/2017: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Added login to work with template
- login template also links to registration page
- Added logout button: once user logged out user can go back
- Username able to appear on homepage
- non-staff/admin users can have access to certain features e.g. Delete button(s)
- site can only be used when user has an account, else redirects to login page
- only one type of user (user role) to login, from there links are provided in the navigation bar
Update 26/10/2017: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- major website/database re-make!
- Users have more fields to registration table to add in (according to requirements)
- Database re-made due to custom users error
- login page navigationbar fixes (hidding elements unless user is logged in)
- navigation tweaks: if user is superuser - can view all elements in navigation bar
- navigation tweaks: if user is normal user - can only view certain elements on the navigation bar
